edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.queue.adt

Class ArrayQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.queue.adt.ArrayQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of all objects to store in the queue
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    QueueInterface<T>

    public final class ArrayQueue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements QueueInterface<T>
    A class that implements the ADT queue by using an expandable circular array.
    Version:
    4.0, 5.0, 4.1.0
    • initial version based upon Carrano and Henry implementation in the 4th edition of the textbook
    • modified per assignment
    , 5.1.0 2019-07-14
    • simplified determination of parameters to System.arraycopy() in ensureCapacity()
    • revisions to match:
      • the 5th edition of the textbook
      • Dave Rosenberg Company coding standard
      • this semester's assignment
    , 5.2.0 2019-10-23 revise for this semester, 5.3.0 2020-03-01
    • update to coding standard
    • switch from QueueInterface to TestableQueueInterface
    , 5.4.0 2020-06-21 rename isFull() to isArrayFull() to more accurately describe its functionality, 5.4.1 2020-06-26 fix ensureCapacity() - was overwriting the contents of the original array rather than copying them into the new array, 5.5.0 2020-10-22
    • switch back to QueueInterface instead of TestableQueueInterface
    • remove size() and toArray()
    • add toString() to aid debugging
    • implement main() to aid debugging
    , 5.6.0 2020-10-22 changes per lab assignment
    Author:
    Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, David M Rosenberg, Your Name
